    • Method Detail

      • computeBlockId

        public static long computeBlockId(int inodeId,
                  int blockIndex)
        Compute the block id based on its inode id and its index among all blocks of the inode. In Tachyon, blockId is calculated by ((inodeId << 30) + blockIndex).
        Parameters:
        inodeId - The inode id of the block
        blockIndex - The index of the block in the inode
        Returns:
        the block id

      • computeBlockIndex

        public static int computeBlockIndex(long blockId)
        Compute the index of a block within its inode based on the block id. The blockIndex is the 30 least significant bits (LSBs) of the blockId.
        Parameters:
        blockId - The id of the block
        Returns:
        the index of the block in the inode

      • computeInodeId

        public static int computeInodeId(long blockId)
        Compute the inode id of the block. The inodeId is the 34 most significant bits (MSBs) of the blockId.
        Parameters:
        blockId - The id of the block
        Returns:
        the inode id of the block

      • addLocation

        public void addLocation(long workerId,
               NetAddress workerAddress,
               long storageDirId)
        Add a location of the block. It means that the worker has the data of the block in memory.
        Parameters:
        workerId - The id of the worker
        workerAddress - The net address of the worker
        storageDirId - The id of the StorageDir which block is located in

      • generateClientBlockInfo

        the generated ClientBlockInfo

      • getBlockIdWorkerIdPairs

        public List<Pair<Long,Long>> getBlockIdWorkerIdPairs()
        Get the list of pairs "blockId, workerId", where the blockId is the id of this block, and the workerId is the id of the worker who has the block's data in memory.
        Returns:
        the list of those pairs

      • getLocations

        public List<NetAddress> getLocations(TachyonConf tachyonConf)
        Get the locations of the block, which are the workers' net address who has the data of the block in its tiered storage. The list is sorted by the storage level alias(MEM, SSD, HDD). That is, the worker who has the data of the block in its memory is in the top of the list.
        Returns:
        the net addresses of the locations

      • isInMemory

        public boolean isInMemory()
        Returns:
        true if the block is in some worker's memory, false otherwise
